%OPTION  ===>_ZCMD

%                      'USING'  primary command
+                      ------------------------

  Primary command USING allows you define base register and specify its
position. This action is pretty similar to the assembler USING command.

  The format of primary command USING is:

 %U{SING}#Offset1/*/Offset2(Reg2)/@Name+#Reg1+#{Offset3/<cursor>}+

  You may type up to three operands. Two first must be specified, third
optional.

  First and second operands of command define offset or DSECT name and n
of the base register. Third operand defines the displacement, where the
assembler command must appear in project listing. If third operand is om
then Offset3 is set equal to Offset1.

